/*             Product Key Verification GUI Sample

WHAT’S HAPPENING
GUI Layout
   • Text prompts the user to enter a key.
   • Edit box lets the user type it.
   • Button runs the validation when clicked (gok label).
   • Text (disp) displays whether the key is valid or invalid.


Q:  What is needle?
       • needle := "^[A-Z][TUVXYZ][5-9](?:[b-g]|[3-6])(?:[A-F]|[b-e])$"
A:  This is a custom pattern to validate a 5-character product key:
   • [A-Z] - The 1st character must be a single uppercase letter A–Z.
   • [TUVXYZ] - The 2nd character must be one of these uppercase letters: T, U, V, X, Y, or Z.
   • [5-9] - The 3rd character must be a digit from 5 to 9.
   • (?:[b-g]|[3-6]) - The 4th character must be either:
       * a lowercase letter from b to g, or
       * a digit from 3 to 6.
   • (?:[A-F]|[b-e]) - The 5th character must be either:
       * an uppercase letter from A to F, or
       * a lowercase letter from b to e.
Other Notes:
   • The ^ (caret) at the start and $ (dollar) at the end ensure that the entire string must match exactly...no extra characters before or after.
   • (?: ... ) is a non-capturing group, used to combine choices like [b-g] or [3-6] without affecting the match index.


Function pk()
    pk(_search, _pattern, _case := 0)
   • _search: what the user typed.
   • _pattern: the needle defined above.
   • _case: 1 = case-sensitive, 0 = case-insensitive.
The function checks:  
    RegExMatch(_search, "\b(" . _pattern . ")\b")
That means the entire string must match the pattern exactly, with word boundaries at start/end.  If it matches, it returns 1, else 0.
;;∙============================================================∙
*/

needle := "^[A-Z][TUVXYZ][5-9](?:[b-g]|[3-6])(?:[A-F]|[b-e])$"

Gui, Add, Text, x6 y8 w130 h20, Please Enter your key.
Gui, Add, Edit, x6 y28 w130 h20 vkey,
Gui, Add, Button, x6 y48 w130 h20 gok, Check
Gui, Add, Text, x146 y8 w150 h60 +Center vdisp,
Gui, Show, , Registration Key Sample.
Return

ok:
    Gui, Submit, NoHide
    jj := pk(key, needle, 1)    ;;∙------∙Case-sensitive match.

    If jj
        GuiControl, Text, disp, The key `"%key%`" is valid.
    Else
        GuiControl, Text, disp, The key `"%key%`" is invalid.`n`nPlease try again.
